’Femi Asu Shell’s subsidiaries in Nigeria have presented eight vehicles to the governments of Lagos and Rivers states to support the efforts at contact tracing and treatment of novel coronavirus cases. The companies, comprising Shell Petroleum Development Company of Nigeria Limited, Shell Nigeria Exploration and Production Company, and Shell Nigeria Gas, also joined other players in the oil and gas industry to support the Federal Government with $30m to stop the spread of the deadly disease. The companies in a statement on Thursday said equipment donated included defibrillators, ventilators, stretchers, swabs, personal protection equipment, and a 150kva generator. Copyright PUNCH.
